Subject: [experiment] ESM4 live rig bounds telemetry

Status: experiment, not queued in patches/openmw/series.
Proof baseline: run/proof-harness-sweeps/20260707-213811.

The FO3/FNV six-shot actor proof shows source skinning as a coherent frozen
containment baseline while current skinning disassembles human actors. Add
live/current-pose rig bounds and last-frame render geometry reporting so the
next proof run can distinguish stale render geometry from bad skinning math.

This patch is measurement-first: it does not change the selected skinning mode
or force a visual fallback.

